The battery
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The vision is brief and fruitless.
You find yourself in front of the monolith, unable to unite with Mary.


<font:speech> "Kicked out by that cry again?" <font:narration>


Alisa's voice carries a note of melancholy.


You nod, puzzled by her mood. <font:speech> "It is as if she does not let me through." <font:narration>


<font:speech> "What will you do?" <font:narration> 


You shrug. <font:speech> "I don't know." <font:narration>


<font:speech> "Well, you should find out fast. If you still want my precious company, that is." <font:narration>


<font:speech> "What are you talking about?" <font:narration> 


You look at the assistant device and notice a small yellow indicator blinking.


<font:speech> "The battery," <font:narration> Alisa says. <font:speech> "It is almost depleted."
